# Test Conduct Deep UI Redesign & Navigation Restrictions

This plan outlines the changes required to align the test conduct flow (Instructions, Testing, Review, Results) with the structural layouts and functionality provided in the screenshots. It includes the strict navigation rules requested.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Strict Navigation Rule**: 
> In testing mode, the user will only be able to click on questions in the sidebar palette if they have already visited them. They cannot skip ahead by clicking future question numbers in the palette; they must use the "Save & Next", "Clear", or "Mark for Review" buttons to progress sequentially.
> **Review Mode Rule**:
> On the Review screen, clicking a question in the grid will *only* navigate back to the question if that question was marked for review (Yellow Star). Regular attempted/not attempted questions cannot be revisited.

