> Regarding the Test Runner navigation: Currently, the old platform requires you to just click "Save & Next" to step through the test. If a student leaves a question completely blank and clicks "Save & Next", we will consider that "Skipped" (Not Attempted) but "Visited" (meaning they can go back to it via the sidebar because they unlocked it). Is this correct?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A - Visual UI layout restructuring.

### Manual Verification
1. Access the test instructions preview visually.
2. Enter testing mode and attempt to click a future unvisited question in the palette (must be denied/disabled).
3. Attempt to jump back to a *visited* question (must be allowed).
4. Go to Review Mode. Attempt to click a green/grey circle (must be inert). Click a yellow star circle (must jump back to that question).
5. Load result page, verify grid of Red/Green/Grey bubbles, and verify modal opens on click.
